accountId().details: This function MUST return a string in the format "vendor.account.semver". The vendor and account names MUST NOT contain a period character.

returns._0: entryPoint The entry point for this account

params.target: The target address for the account to call.
params.value: The value to send with the call.

returns.result: The return data from the call.

executeBatch((address,uint256,bytes)[]).details: If the target is a module, the call SHOULD revert. If any of the calls revert, the entire batch MUST revert.

returns.results: An array containing the return data from the calls.

executeUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,byt.details: This function is only callable by the EntryPoint

params.userOp: - The operation that was just validated.
params.userOpHash: - Hash of the user's request data.

params.authorization: The authorization data to use for the call. The first 24 bytes is a ModuleEntity which specifies which runtime validation to use, and the rest is sent as a parameter to runtime validation.
params.data: The calldata to send to the account.

getExecutionData(bytes4).details: If the selector is a native function, the module address will be the address of the account.

params.selector: The selector to get the data for.

returns.data: The execution data for this selector.

returns._0: The fallback signer address, either overriden in storage, or read from bytecode.

getValidationData(bytes24).details: If the selector is a native function, the module address will be the address of the account.

params.validationFunction: The validation function to get the data for.

returns.data: The validation data for this validation function.

params.installData: Optional data to be used by the account to handle the initial execution setup. Data encoding is implementation-specific.
params.manifest: the manifest describing functions to install.

installValidation(bytes25,bytes4[],bytes.details: This function can be used to update (to a certain degree) previously installed validation functions.      - preValidationHook, executionHooks, and selectors can be added later. Though they won't be deleted.      - isGlobal and isSignatureValidation can also be updated later.

params.hooks: Optional hooks to install and associate with the validation function. Data encoding is implementation-specific.
params.installData: Optional data to be used by the account to handle the initial validation setup. Data encoding is implementation-specific.
params.selectors: The selectors to install the validation function for.
params.validationConfig: The validation function to install, along with configuration flags.

returns._0: True if the fallback signer validation is disabled, false if it is enabled.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Should return whether the signature provided is valid for the provided data

params.hash: Hash of the data to be signed

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

setFallbackSignerDisabled(bool).details: Due to being initially zero, we need to store "disabled" rather than "enabled" in storage.

params.isDisabled: True to disable fallback signer validation, false to enable it.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: returns true for `IERC165.interfaceId` and false for `0xFFFFFFFF`

params.manifest: the manifest describing functions to uninstall.
params.uninstallData: Optional data to be used by the account to handle the execution uninstallation. Data encoding is implementation-specific.

params.hookUninstallData: Optional data to be used by the account to handle hook uninstallation. Data encoding is implementation-specific.
params.uninstallData: Optional data to be used by the account to handle the validation uninstallation. Data encoding is implementation-specific.

updateFallbackSigner(address).details: This function causes the fallback signer getter to ignore the bytecode signer if it is nonzero. It can also be used to revert back to the bytecode signer by setting to zero.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: Must validate caller is the entryPoint.      Must validate the signature and nonce

params.missingAccountFunds: - Missing funds on the account's deposit in the entrypoint.                              This is the minimum amount to transfer to the sender(entryPoint) to be                              able to make the call. The excess is left as a deposit in the entrypoint                              for future calls. Can be withdrawn anytime using "entryPoint.withdrawTo()".                              In case there is a paymaster in the request (or the current deposit is high                              enough), this value will be zero.
params.userOp: - The operation that is about to be executed.
params.userOpHash: - Hash of the user's request data. can be used as the basis for signature.

returns.validationData: - Packaged ValidationData structure. use `_packValidationData` and                              `_unpackValidationData` to encode and decode.                              <20-byte> sigAuthorizer - 0 for valid signature, 1 to mark signature failure,                                 otherwise, an address of an "authorizer" contract.                              <6-byte> validUntil - Last timestamp this operation is valid. 0 for "indefinite"                              <6-byte> validAfter - First timestamp this operation is valid                                                    If an account doesn't use time-range, it is enough to                                                    return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED value (1) for signature failure.                              Note that the validation code cannot use block.timestamp (or block.number) directly.

accountId().notice: Return a unique identifier for the account implementation.

entryPoint().notice: Gets the entry point for this account

execute(address,uint256,bytes).notice: May be validated by a global validation.

executeBatch((address,uint256,bytes)[]).notice: May be validated by a global validation function.

executeUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,byt.notice: Execution function that allows UO context to be passed to execution hooks

executeWithRuntimeValidation(bytes,bytes.notice: Execute a call using the specified runtime validation.

getExecutionData(bytes4).notice: Get the execution data for a selector.

getFallbackSigner().notice: Returns the fallback signer associated with this account, regardless if the fallback signer validation is enabled or not.

getNonce().notice: Return the account nonce. This method returns the next sequential nonce. For a nonce of a specific key, use `entrypoint.getNonce(account, key)`

getValidationData(bytes24).notice: Get the validation data for a validation function.

initializeWithValidation(bytes25,bytes4[.notice: Override reverts on initialization, effectively disabling the initializer.

installExecution(address,((bytes4,bool,b.notice: May be validated by a global validation.

installValidation(bytes25,bytes4[],bytes.notice: May be validated by a global validation.

isFallbackSignerDisabled().notice: Returns whether the fallback signer validation is disabled.

setFallbackSignerDisabled(bool).notice: Sets whether the fallback signer validation should be enabled or disabled.

uninstallExecution(address,((bytes4,bool.notice: May be validated by a global validation.

uninstallValidation(bytes24,bytes,bytes[.notice: May be validated by a global validation.

updateFallbackSigner(address).notice: Updates the fallback signer address in storage.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).notice: May be validated by a global validation.

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.notice: Validate user's signature and nonce the entryPoint will make the call to the recipient only if this validation call returns successfully. signature failure should be reported by returning SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED (1). This allows making a "simulation call" without a valid signature Other failures (e.g. nonce mismatch, or invalid signature format) should still revert to signal failure.
